enoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Shelley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the three places called Shelley (Essex, Suffolk, Yorkshire) or from Shelley Plain in Crawley (Sussex). The placenames all derive from Old English <i>scelf</i> ‘rock, ledge, shelf’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish (Laois): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Sealbhaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Sealbhach</i>’, a byname from the adjective <i>sealbhach</i> ‘having possessions, wealthy’."],"variants":[{"name":"Shallow","meanings":["Irish (Kilkenny and Wexford): variant of   Shelley  .","English: nickname from Middle English <i>shalou(e)</i> ‘shallow’, conjectured also to mean ‘thin’; perhaps also the same word in the topographic sense of ‘shallow place in a stretch of water’.","Americanized form of French   Chalut  ."]},{"name":"Shelly","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Shelley  ."]},{"name":"Shealy","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Shelley  ."]},{"name":"Sheeley","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Shelley  ."]},{"name":"Sheely","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Shelley  ."]},{"name":"Sheley","meanings":["Irish and English: variant of   Shelley  ."]}]},{"name":"Eustace","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old French form of the Late Greek names <i>Eustakhios</i> and <i>Eustathios</i>. These were evidently of separate origin, the former derived from <i>eu</i> ‘well, good’ + <i>stakhys</i> ‘grapes’, the latter from <i>eu</i> + <i>stēnai</i> ‘to stand’. However, the tradition is very confused. The name was introduced in this form to Britain by the Normans, among whom it was popular as a result of the fame of  St Eustace , a Norman nobleman who was said to have been converted to Christianity by the vision of a crucifix between the antlers of the stag he was hunting."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eustace De Shelley was born in 1130, his father, Eustace (of SHELLEY) de SELLEA, was 30 and his mother, albreda shelley, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Emma. He died on 3 July 1157, in Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 27."},"et":{"1130–3 Jul 1157":"1130–3. juuli 1157","1130–1157":"1130–1157","–Female":"Surnud","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1145–1182":"1145–1182","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1106–1170":"1106–1170","1106":"1106","1115":"1115","1157":"1157","1145":"1145","1100":"1100","1130":"1130","about 1145":"umbes 1145","3 Jul 1157":"3. juuli 1157","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","1170":"1170","North Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Shelley, Essex, England":"Shelley, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1130–3 Jul 1157":"1130–3. heinäkuuta 1157","1130–1157":"1130–1157","–Female":"Kuollut","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1145–1182":"1145–1182","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1106–1170":"1106–1170","1106":"1106","1115":"1115","1157":"1157","1145":"1145","1100":"1100","1130":"1130","about 1145":"noin 1145","3 Jul 1157":"3. heinäkuuta 1157","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","1170":"1170","North Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shelley, Essex, England":"Shelley, Essex, England"},"fr":{"1130–3 Jul 1157":"1130–3 juillet 1157","1130–1157":"1130–1157","–Female":"Décédée","1115–Female":"1115–Décédée","1145–1182":"1145–1182","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1100–Male":"1100–Décédé","1106–1170":"1106–1170","1106":"1106","1115":"1115","1157":"1157","1145":"1145","1100":"1100","1130":"1130","about 1145":"environ 1145","3 Jul 1157":"3 juillet 1157","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","1170":"1170","North Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Shelley, Essex, England":"Shelley, Essex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Eustace De Shelley est né en 1130, son père, Eustace (of SHELLEY) de SELLEA, avait 30 ans et sa mère, albreda shelley, 